refore, I simply abandoned the flat, telling the maid to dispose inany manner she chose of all those unwanted things. Unwanted! At the momentof parting they appeared quite normal and harmless; I would even say theylooked taken aback.

At first I tried putting up in a third-rate hotel in the center ofParis. I would fight terror and solitude by working all day. I completed onenovel, began another, wrote forty poems (all robbers and brothers undertheir motley <73> skin), a dozen short stories, seve